---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import PhilosophyCallout from '../../components/docs/PhilosophyCallout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Errors & warnings" description="Cleo error and warning state patterns">
  <div class="prose">
    <h1>Error and warning states</h1>
    <p class="page-lead">Errors are rare, plain, and actionable. Warnings are guardians, not alarms.</p>

    <h2>Warnings</h2>
    <p>Amber border and background tint. Plain English explanation. Suggested fix inline. Used for denial risk — Frame 6.</p>

    <h2>Errors</h2>
    <p>Reserved for blocked submission or system failure. Muted red — never bright #FF0000. State what happened and the single next step.</p>

    <h2>Never</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Modal stacks for recoverable issues</li>
      <li>Exclamation icons on every validation</li>
      <li>Red for denial suggestions (that's what competitors do)</li>
    </ul>

    <PhilosophyCallout>
      <p>Frame 2 trauma around denials means red triggers fight-or-flight. Amber says "let's look at this together."</p>
    </PhilosophyCallout>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
